# Project Preamble: ClinicalMatchMaker

## Language & Framework
- TypeScript with strict mode enabled
- React 18+ for frontend components
- Vite as build tool
- Tailwind CSS for styling

## Coding Conventions
- Use functional components with hooks (no class components)
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use async/await over raw promises
- Use Zod for runtime validation at boundaries
- Destructure props in function signatures
- Use camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for types/components

## Error Handling
- Throw typed errors with descriptive messages
- Use try-catch at service boundaries
- Log errors before rethrowing
- Provide user-friendly error messages in UI components

## Security & Privacy
- Never log patient identifiable information
- Validate all external API responses
- Sanitize user inputs before display
- Use HTTPS for all external API calls

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include ARIA labels where appropriate
- Support keyboard navigation
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA compliance

## Medical Disclaimer
- All user-facing outputs must acknowledge this is informational only
- Include disclaimer: "Always consult with a qualified healthcare provider"
